The paper deals with planning the path of a camera-equipped UAV for visual inspection applications, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The proposed method involves generating via-points and path primitives, which can be considered as a form of sampling-based planning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses encoding topological information and performing graph search, which are related to graph theory (cs.GR) and control systems (cs.SY).
